6:
The guild's pretty spiffy, but it's got 
nothing on a place like this!
8:
There's so much room! Not to mention 
Alk's crazy good cooking! And on top 
of that, people here actually respect 
me as a dragon!
11:
I'm glad you've found this place to 
your liking.
14:
Yup! You and your crew are set, now 
that you've got DRAGON power on 
your side!
18:
Anyone who even THINKS about 
stepping up to us is toast!
20:
I mean, who would even try to fight 
a dragon, right?
23:
Just the mere mention is enough to 
send most people home!
26:
True. The history of dragons in 
Palpebra is one rooted in vast 
destruction.
28:
And yet, some defied the dragons, 
taking them down and claiming the 
title of Dragon Slayer.
31:
Yeah, well... I bet they had some totally 
epic battles!
35:
I just found it to be curious that you 
had chosen to live with the guild as 
their "mascot" for so long.
38:
I mean, isn't it obvious? Humans are 
fascinating!
43:
They're supposed to be weak, right? 
Compared to dragons, at least.
44:
But when they work together, they can 
overcome all sorts of adversity! I just 
think that's neat.
47:
And there's no better way to learn 
about them than living among them, 
right?
50:
Are you not resentful of the actions of 
their ancestors?
54: You really think I'm that petty?
57:
And besides, I've always been around 
them ever since I hatched.
62:
You've learned the importance of 
having loyal comrades.
67:
I guess you could say that. But 
sometimes I'm not so sure.
70:
But didn't you used to be super 
powerful or something? Why do YOU 
need comrades?
73: Oof... That wound's still a little fresh.
75:
The truth is, it was Alk and the others 
who taught me the importance of 
camaraderie.
79:
I thought that might've been the case. 
I guess that's why you're training him, 
right?
89:
You're training him to be your 
successor, right?
92: N-no, that isn't my intention, but—
94:
The burden I carry is not for the faint-
hearted. I don't think he's anywhere 
near ready to be something like—
97:
But you want him to become stronger, 
don'tcha?
104:
That's a good enough reason if you 
ask me! Right?
106:
And if you ask me, the title of Dragon 
Warrior is WAY cooler than Dragon 
Slayer!
109:
I suppose it wouldn't hurt to oversee 
his potential.
112:
Yeah, we're comrades. And comrades 
stick together!
